# Planning stories

When editing files under `docs/stories/`, follow the `doccraft-story` skill
for the YAML frontmatter contract (`id`, `title`, `status`, `impact`,
`urgency`, `tags`, `openspec`, `depends_on`, …), tag vocabulary
(`area:` / `slice:` / `theme:` prefixes), and enum values.

Each `depends_on` entry must be an `id` that exists on another story, or a
deliberate backlog-only prerequisite documented in **Notes**. Do not invent
fake ids.

## After new stories or dependency edits

When you create a new story or change `depends_on` / `id` in a way that
affects ordering, invoke the `doccraft-queue-audit` skill in the same turn
so the queue, backlog, and story frontmatter stay consistent.
